Following these steps should resolve the job failure. For more context, review the merge-gate-interface.yml and improvements doc in your repository. and I'll analyze the failing job logs to identify the issue and provide a solution.## Solution

The job is failing because the stop-and-fix enforcement check is detecting "STOP-AND-FIX" text in documentation and governance files, not actual unresolved stop-and-fix conditions.

Root Cause
The grep pattern on line 203 of the workflow is too broad:

bash
if grep -r "STOP-AND-FIX" --include="*.md" --include="*.txt" . 2>/dev/null; then
It's matching:

./governance/canon/STOP_AND_FIX_DOCTRINE.md - the doctrine definition itself
./governance/canon/WE_ONLY_FAIL_ONCE_DOCTRINE.md - references to the doctrine
./PREHANDOVER_PROOF_archive_20260127_previous.md - archived historical documentation
./.github/agents/legacy/governance-repo-administrator.agent.md - governance documentation
Recommended Fix
Update the workflow at line 203 to exclude governance documentation and archives:

YAML
- name: Check for stop-and-fix conditions
  run: |
    echo "=== Stop-and-Fix Enforcement ===" 
    
    # Check for stop-and-fix markers in code (exclude governance canon and archives)
    if grep -r "STOP-AND-FIX" --include="*.md" --include="*.txt" \
         --exclude-dir=governance \
         --exclude-dir=.github/agents \
         --exclude="*archive*.md" \
         --exclude="*DOCTRINE.md" \
         . 2>/dev/null; then
      echo "‚ùå STOP-AND-FIX condition detected in repository"
      echo ""
      echo "Found unresolved STOP-AND-FIX markers."
      echo "Required action: Resolve the condition and remove the marker"
      echo "Required by: STOP_AND_FIX_DOCTRINE.md"
      exit 1
    fi
Alternative: Use a more specific marker pattern like "TODO: STOP-AND-FIX" or "ACTIVE-STOP-AND-FIX" for actual conditions that need resolution, allowing the term "STOP-AND-FIX" to appear in documentation. The agent must use ALLLL the resources at his disposal, including invoking other agents to resolve the issue

